Quality check 03, List blocks in block groups split by community districts

Satya Golla and Steve Simon

Created 2023-03-30

This program lists blocks within block groups that only partially intersect with community districts.

Load relevant files

# Important abbreviations:
#    bg = block group
#    bl = block
#    cd = community district
#    co = county
#    nbd=neighborhood
#    tr = tract

clist <- c(
  "20091",
  "20103",
  "20209",
  "29037",
  "29047",
  "29095",
  "29165")
co                                     %>%
  filter(GEOID %in% clist)             -> co

Get id values for all community districts

cd                                     %>%
  tibble                               %>%
  distinct(cd_id)                      %>%
  arrange(cd_id)                       %>%
  pull(cd_id)                           -> cd_list

Draw an overview map

co_points <- st_point_on_surface(co)
## Warning in st_point_on_surface.sf(co): st_point_on_surface assumes attributes
## are constant over geometries of x
## Warning in st_point_on_surface.sfc(st_geometry(x)): st_point_on_surface may not
## give correct results for longitude/latitude data
co_coords <- as.data.frame(st_coordinates(co_points))
co_coords$NAME <- co$NAME

ggplot()+
  geom_sf(
    data=co, 
    color="darkred", 
    fill=NA)                            +
  geom_text(
    data=co_coords, 
    aes(X, Y, label=NAME))              +
  xlab("Longitude")                     +
  ylab("Latitude")                      -> overview_map
plot(overview_map)

High level view

i_cd <- interesting_cd[1]
cd %>% pick_cd(i_cd) -> cd0
plot_green(cd0, co, "NAME")      +
  ggtitle(cd0$cd_name)           -> o_map
plot(o_map)
